.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-8-20::.
City: hamburg, london, liverpool, hannover
The people use 4 different means of transport: car, jet-ski, subway, van
1. the person driving the jet-ski is not the person traveling to hamburg##6
2. the person driving the subway is on the right of the person driving the van##1
3. the person traveling to hannover is not to the left of the person driving the van##8
4. the person traveling to liverpool is the person driving the car##1
5. the person traveling to hannover is somewhere between the person driving the jet-ski and the person driving the car##7
6. the person traveling to hannover is on the left of the person traveling to hamburg##1
7. the person driving the subway is between the person driving the van and the person traveling to liverpool##2

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |    2     |     3      |    4    |
| City         | london    | hannover | hamburg | liverpool |
| Transport   | jet-ski | van      | subway     | car     |

 